jectOutputStream.writeObject(...)`\n- Deserializing it through `ObjectInputStream.readObject()`\n- Verifying the restored DSA public key parameters and encoding\n\nThe JVM coverage data shows that both private serialization methods are executed:\n\n- `BCDSAPublicKey.readObject(ObjectInputStream)` — covered\n- `BCDSAPublicKey.writeObject(ObjectOutputStream)` — covered\n\nHowever, the dynamic-access report still marks the call sites as uncovered because the `bcprov-jdk15on:1.48` artifact appears to lack line-number/source debug metadata for this class. Native Image reports the frames as:\n\n`org.bouncycastle.jcajce.provider.asymmetric.dsa.BCDSAPublicKey.readObject(Unknown Source)`\n\nand\n\n`org.bouncycastle.jcajce.provider.asymmetric.dsa.BCDSAPublicKey.writeObject(Unknown Source)`\n\nThe coverage reporter only marks dynamic-access call sites covered when the reported frame includes a source line that can be matched against JaCoCo line coverage. With `Unknown Source` / no line number, the call site cannot be marked covered even though the method is actually reached by the test.\n\nI left the dedicated test in place because it is the correct public-API coverage path for the active class.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0d0a98a2c14211a5016a10bd2acd588190bc7950285d269bf2\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1234, "output": 1388, "cacheRead": 100864, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 103486, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1779481879274, "responseId": "resp_0d0a98a2c14211a5016a10bd18f2588190b54a2b3996e6dbfa"}}
