d I simply perform roundtrip only on the JVM?\n\n**Considering metadata generation**\n\nIn our repository, there's no metadata available. The user stated, \"never write metadata,\" and mentioned that Forge handles metadata generation and merging externally. So, perhaps a native failure is acceptable locally before any metadata is generated. \n\nBut when it comes to the final external build, I assume that metadata will be created. Should I use `RuntimeSerialization` registration in my test feature instead of a metadata file? Is it allowed to register in the feature? It might not be, but can tests include @RegisterForReflection as a workaround? It does feel metadata-like, but maybe I shouldn't rely on it.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0d0a98a2c14211a5016a10bd703024819092bcfc7f336b1d85\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqEL2In-mX6uSFL69XRGrvjbkddiUax1vGYQQcJIKjpsMvfL5Mz87DZRovm_98Q3f1mA_9z7VWDD57hbu8jgG76f2NJgxJw2OTeg71ZYVVBEf-VCl8KZ2kF_lzHLclFIrJSdSB3G6-9D-LohKMLItP0p2oR6_jVip_kPdHjfUK5sWUV-bFem20rMaujcNvXrjoOG_4hmRynWuVVIAg8nC0L2XekeDOTZosV7lsuGEKr2MOXQl3olLahNqzv-mIEusoXvhdHHSpo9jitsQTKBuoduF9KKcJGeD1zT84JqzTyPxL3s5Cq5oSfAVf2KATKp6nbMC6vkqwZ2K32T7ShtvT9Agr3624iep5jj5BceqR0pWHbLWvgt-sP_Rs-BZxvRJoKn1xomYzVWq3FrlAWxM_dAyWr3dcFqnKI-HCXbwUiffZ5fCsNSfv-Zs1aGAvvllbdTKXVNnwu_eLmJ_TBuxuxQQe5hLjvT4obv9dwGaMsgivU2SejZr6_TedFgo8uGFoaR_jh02YcN6q1xd96DGtjbKJbyVIw7CzH0Tw7digBQyAopNoVF4X7zeIurzpl2Mu5OEF1cVMoBlbj8gLFyj94A4HkcagdXfiE_xAU4KwEH3BPzeK4LcPwFVFB3OTVDE2nQFHZ973aqQtMYgQLIjZT-dSGvay-OITirE1S8Xc2GikmeHHQKT8wBpXZluBo5sEsStTGehYl2kDVOxvlfLelpYcu73t8_tWJj08D7mRm9KaKiXc561k2w1FCF7YxRojO3YVFdIJIeLI9FQxU-BQ3DcauR1pubBRO3k0DT6wQbtsZlp0dm_Kx2SBQQi-dMCU3FlSJzsiAVe8VXo6zHwOtU_-vSFaG1-YSvFuSU2D5uKn6YwNdIPDuA7yv1X3DDeNZmhrDxwvNFQv6ahe48NW3UyqWJBUuGJqjljf647rTrLKCc-dzT6DwUTJ4keFBOeszdf4oKZlbLM_cE2s6uP1k0K1_Fph0gq37etfQRjfbG_p4SZmUxk_9pUkN0H0NGlepRJQWmvVUSHx8HqR0ZZ5N22yliPJ-nYd88KtqGxB2U__8b5dy0jTsudVvM6StZzCubF3Fe2eZbBoNhnawFwTE_-vTWq1OsHoZLWsqSyYHgBICN0g2FsXwD